                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" id="alabama_sng_1" hclass="sense" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">a southern US state, also called the Yellowhammer State, the Cotton State and the Heart of <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/dixie#dixie_sng_1" title="Dixie definition"><span class="ndv">Dixie</span></a>. The capital city is <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/montgomery" title="Montgomery definition"><span class="ndv">Montgomery</span></a> and the largest city is <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/birmingham" title="Birmingham definition"><span class="ndv">Birmingham</span></a>. Important industries include the production of paper, <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/textile#textile_topg_1" title="textiles definition"><span class="ndv">textiles</span></a>, chemicals and metals. It also has many farm products, including milk, <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/wheat" title="wheat definition"><span class="ndv">wheat</span></a> and cotton.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
